name: raven-and-raptor-power-line-mortality-data-in-the-moon-lake-electrical-association-se-1995-2002
notes: Data in the form of spreadsheets are the results of searches for dead birds along 1-phase and 3-phase power line segments and at individual poles in the Moon lake Electrical Association service area in northeastern Utah and western Colorado from June 2001-October 2004. Data include mortalities found during randomized pole surveys in the Rangely Oil Field (ROF) in western Colorado, conducted quarterly from July 2001-May 2003, ROF pole censuses conducted monthly from August 2003-August 2004. Data also include mortalities resulting from surveys of randomly selected 2-km and 5-km power line segments conducted throughout the Moon Lake service area from September 2001-May 2003, incidental mortalities found and reported by Moon Lake and other study cooperators, and historical mortality records, dating from September 1992-May 2001, provided by Moon Lake.
